The Writing Center is hosting a "Wacky Writing Extravaganza!"  Each participant will be given FREE candy, just for participating, and THREE lucky and talented winners will each win a big tub of candy!

Where:  In the Writing Center (A109)

When:  TODAY, Wednesday and Thursday (April 12-14)

What:  You'll be given a wacky writing prompt and you'll have FIVE minutes to write a short story in which you use the items listed in the prompt (a fun, random assortment of items and people)

Contest is open to students, faculty and staff!  Winners will be announced Friday afternoon.

~Ms. Micklo & the Writing Center Staff 